"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533877","Home Office","false","2016-07-12","<p>Counter-terrorism checks conducted by the Home Office form part of the national security vetting process required for employment in the Home Office.</p><p>We continue to reduce the processing time for all national security vetting checks. Processing times will vary from case to case and are not broken down by constituent parts of the UK.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2016-07-12T16:11:45.577Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533877/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533877/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533877/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-07-08","Vetting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make an assessment of the time taken to process counter-terrorism checks for job applications in (a) Northern Ireland and (b) other constituent parts of the UK.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","42255"
