"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533387","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-07-11","<p>Full-time students starting nursing courses from 1 August 2017 will qualify for the same loans for living costs as other new full-time undergraduate students in 2017/18. Loans for living costs are paid to students in three equal instalments at the start of each term to help meet up-front costs while studying.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-07-11T15:54:16.92Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533387/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533387/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-07-06","Nurses: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will make it his policy that student maintenance loan payments are paid on a monthly basis to nursing students.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","42032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533388","Department of Health","false","2016-07-11","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>Data on waiting lists for Care and Treatment Reviews (CTRs) is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>The number of CTRs completed was added to the Health and Social Care Information Centre‘s Assuring Transformation Collection and data has been collected since January 2016. Between January 2016 and May 2016, 625 CTRs have been completed.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-07-11T15:28:06.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533388/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533388/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-06","Learning Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people with learning disabilities are on the waiting list for a Care and Treatment Review.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","42043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533389","Department of Health","false","2016-07-13","<p>A preliminary Economic Impact Assessment and Equality Analysis was published alongside the public consultation launched on 7 April 2016. These documents address the proportion of repayment expected, the impact on students with different characteristics, including those who live outside the parental home and the benefit that extra support will have for those on low incomes and from disadvantaged backgrounds.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-07-13T13:38:13.84Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533389/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533389/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-06","Nurses: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effect of the removal of nursing bursaries on the living costs of nursing students who live outside their parental home.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","42033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533390","Department of Health","false","2016-07-13","<p>This is a matter for NHS England. NHS England advises that the second part of its review of the UnitingCare Partnership limited liability partnership contract is looking at specific areas, including the role of external advisors, and will be used to inform and improve its internal processes. PricewaterhouseCoopers is currently completing the first draft of the review. NHS England expects to receive this imminently, and the report will then be finalised over the next few weeks. The arrangements for publicising the report are a matter for NHS England.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-07-13T15:13:53.637Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533390/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533390/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-06","Cambridgeshire and Peterborough Clinical Commissioning Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to pages 17 and 20 of the NHS England Review of Uniting Care Contract, published in April 2016, when he expects NHS England's review into the role, function and effectiveness of advisors involved in the Cambridgeshire and Peterborough Clinical Commissioning Group contract procurement to be published.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","42040"
