"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533412","Department of Health","false","2016-07-13","<p>All prisons in England are required to have drug treatment programmes for inmates with addictions.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has allocated approximately £405 million for health expenditure in the adult prison estate in 2016/17, with spending on substance misuse services expected to amount to approximately 20% of this.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-07-13T13:34:42.593Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533412/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533412/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533412/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-06","Prisons: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will list the prison establishments that currently run drug treatment programmes for inmates with addictions; and what estimate he has made of the annual cost of running such programmes.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","42009"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533413","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-07-11","<p>Information about the frequency of emergency call-outs to prisons is not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-07-11T14:36:04.253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533413/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533413/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533413/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-07-06","Prisons: Emergency Calls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many 999 calls were made by each prison establishment as a result of substance misuse including alcohol and new psychoactive substances in the last six months; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","42010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533414","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-07-11","<p>The Learning and Skills and Prison Industries Competitions are both in progress. The final evaluation criteria is under development and details are neither finalised nor in the public domain. On that basis the draft evaluation criteria which detail the weightings are currently commercially sensitive and cannot be released at this stage.</p><p> </p><p>However, the contracts for both services will include clauses requiring compliance in relation to Welsh language. The evaluation takes into account a variety of measures and the assessment of Welsh language is being considered as part of the on-going work to finalise evaluation criteria and other tender documentation.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-07-11T10:49:35.193Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533414/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533414/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533414/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-07-06","Berwyn Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what weight is given to the ability to provide services in the Welsh language when assessing tenders for (a) learning and skills and (b) industries at HM Prison Berwyn.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","42013"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533415","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-07-11","<p>NOMS publishes the Prison Population and Operational Capacity figures every Friday, at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/prison-population-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/prison-population-statistics</a></p><p> </p><p>We are committed to ensuring that there are enough places for offenders sentenced to custody by the courts and in providing safe, decent and secure places for those held in custody.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-07-11T11:05:57.083Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533415/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533415/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533415/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-07-06","Prisons: Overcrowding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether the prison population was above its operational capacity in the most recent period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","42062"
