"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533419","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-07-14","<p>Since 2010, my Department has spent £3.96m on information technology and equipment, including IT support and maintenance. This represents expenditure up to the end of the 2015-16 financial year.</p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2016-07-14T10:19:47.643Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533419/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533419/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533419/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-07-06","Northern Ireland Office: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how much her Department has spent on information technology and equipment since 2010.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","41985"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533420","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-07-14","<p>I have regular discussions on implementation of the Fresh Start Agreement with the Minister of Justice for Northern Ireland and the Chief Constable of the Police Service of Northern Ireland. I attended a review meeting on implementation of the Fresh Start Agreement on 29 June 2016 with the Northern Ireland Executive and the Government of Ireland. I have not had any recent discussions with the Northern Ireland Policing Board on implementation of the agreement.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2016-07-14T10:31:05.047Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533420/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533420/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533420/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-07-06","Stormont House Agreement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what recent discussions she has had with the Northern Ireland Policing Board about the implementation of the Fresh Start Agreement.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","41986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533421","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-07-12","<p>I meet the Chief Constable of the Police Service of Northern Ireland on a regular basis to discuss a range of security issues.</p><p>Community-based policing in Northern Ireland is an operational matter which rests solely with the Chief Constable.</p><p><br></p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2016-07-12T10:13:06.827Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533421/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533421/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533421/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-07-06","Community Policing: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what recent discussions she has had with the Northern Ireland Executive on community-based policing.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","41987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533422","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-07-14","<p>There is currently 1 PSNI officer per 273 of the population in Northern Ireland.</p><p>The answers for part (b) and (c) are matters for the Home Office.</p><p><br></p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2016-07-14T10:29:04.527Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533422/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533422/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533422/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-07-06","Police: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many police officers there are per head of population (a) in Northern Ireland, (b) in the Metropolitan Police Service area and (c) on average for all police forces in the UK.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","41988"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533423","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-07-12","<p>I met representatives from the Police Federation of Northern Ireland (PFNI) in December 2015 to discuss a range of issues. The Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Northern Ireland also met the PFNI in March 2016.</p><p>Levels of recruitment are an operational matter for the Chief Constable of the Police Service of Northern Ireland.</p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2016-07-12T10:14:26.903Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533423/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533423/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533423/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-07-06","Police Service of Northern Ireland: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what recent discussions she has had with the Police Federation of Northern Ireland on levels of recruitment to the Police Service of Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","41989"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533424","Prime Minister","false","2016-07-11","<p>I refer my hon. Friend to the answer I gave to my hon. Friend the Member for Filton and Bradley Stoke (Mr Lopresti) during my Oral Statement on the Report of the Iraq Inquiry on 6 July 2016, <em>Official Report</em>, column 904.</p><p> </p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2016-07-11T16:09:13.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533424/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533424/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533424/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-07-06","Armed Conflict: Parliamentary Scrutiny","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if the Government will bring forward legislative proposals to give Parliament a veto on proposed future military action.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","41990"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533425","Cabinet Office","false","2016-07-11","<p>The running of a public inquiry is normally a matter for the independent Chair. However, good practice is that when establishing a public inquiry, Departments should seek to include in the terms of reference an estimate of the likely duration of the Inquiry.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-07-11T08:41:13.13Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533425/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533425/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533425/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-07-06","Public Inquiries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if the Government will bring forward proposals to limit the duration of public inquiries.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","41991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533427","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-11","<p>It is not for the Department to approve changes to the timetable. GTR has informed us of their intention to change the timetable in order to provide a more reliable timetable for passengers.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-07-11T15:36:48.99Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533427/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533427/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533427/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-07-06","Southern: Timetables","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, on what date the emergency timetable for Southern rail services to be introduced by Govia Thameslink Railway from 11 July 2016 was agreed by his Department; and what consultation his Department undertook on that timetable prior to its agreement.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","41997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533428","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-11","<p>Under the Franchise Agreement, where GTR can provide the evidence that cancellations are due to official or unofficial industrial action, they can claim Force Majeure, which they have done. The Govia Thameslink Railway Franchise Agreement in Schedule 7.1 sets out the performance benchmarks and financial regime that is in place in relation to cancellations. A copy of the Franchise Agreement can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/govia-thameslink" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/govia-thameslink</a> .</p><p>The department is monitoring the position on a regular basis.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","42000 ; 42001","2016-07-11T16:37:29.09Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533428/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533428/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533428/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-07-06","Govia Thameslink Railway: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many (a) planned and (b) unplanned train service cancellations in each reporting period would place Govia Thameslink Railway in breach of the Remedial Plan agreed with his Department in February 2016.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","41998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533429","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-11","<p>We monitor GTR’s performance and we have ongoing discussions with them over the delivery of their train services.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-07-11T15:33:10.35Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533429/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533429/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533429/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-07-06","Govia Thameslink Railway: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions his Department has had with Govia Thameslink Railway on the threshold for (a) planned and (b) unplanned train service cancellations since February 2016.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","41999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533430","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-11","<p>Under the Franchise Agreement, where GTR can provide the evidence that cancellations are due to official or unofficial industrial action, they can claim Force Majeure, which they have done. The Govia Thameslink Railway Franchise Agreement in Schedule 7.1 sets out the performance benchmarks and financial regime that is in place in relation to cancellations. A copy of the Franchise Agreement can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/govia-thameslink" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/govia-thameslink</a> .</p><p>The department is monitoring the position on a regular basis.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","41998 ; 42001","2016-07-11T16:37:29.2Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533430/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533430/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533430/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-07-06","Govia Thameslink Railway: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many (a) planned and (b) unplanned cancellations of train services operated by Govia Thameslink Railway (GTR) under the emergency timetable introduced from 11 July 2016 would place GTR in breach of the level of cancellations set out in the Remedial Plan agreed between GTR and his Department in February 2016.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","42000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533431","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-11","<p>Under the Franchise Agreement, where GTR can provide the evidence that cancellations are due to official or unofficial industrial action, they can claim Force Majeure, which they have done. The Govia Thameslink Railway Franchise Agreement in Schedule 7.1 sets out the performance benchmarks and financial regime that is in place in relation to cancellations. A copy of the Franchise Agreement can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/govia-thameslink" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/govia-thameslink</a> .</p><p>The department is monitoring the position on a regular basis.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","41998 ; 42000","2016-07-11T16:37:28.95Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533431/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533431/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533431/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-07-06","Southern: Timetables","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the emergency timetable for Southern Rail services to be introduced from 11 July 2016 is in breach of the level of planned service train cancellations set out in the Remedial Plan agreed between Govia Thameslink Railway and his Department in February 2016.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","42001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533432","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-11","<p>Officials in my Department have regular discussions with representatives of the aviation sector on a range of issues.</p><p> </p><p>The Government’s position on the outcome of the EU referendum is clear: the British people voted for the UK to leave the European Union on 23 June and their will must be respected and delivered.</p><p> </p><p>And as My Right Honourable Friend the Prime Minister has said, it will be for the Government, under a new Prime Minister, to begin negotiations to exit the EU. Until exit negotiations are concluded, the UK remains a full member of the European Union and all the rights and obligations of EU membership remain in force. During this period the Government will continue to negotiate, implement and apply EU legislation.</p><p> </p><p>There will be no immediate changes to our aviation priorities as a consequence of the vote, and the Government will continue working to deliver its agenda.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-07-11T14:24:33.863Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533432/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533432/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533432/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-07-06","Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 6 July to Question 41425, what discussions his Department has had with representatives of the UK aviation sector on the implications for (a) that sector and (b) the priorities for his Department's aviation policies of the outcome of the referendum on the UK's membership of the EU.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","42056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533433","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-11","<p>The successful bidder will help us realise our ambitious plans for East Anglia’s rail network. We have been clear that as a minimum they must provide a modern service with state of the art trains and also introduce at least two 90-minute services each way between London and Norwich. In addition they must invest heavily in improving stations.</p><p> </p><p>We advised an anticipated date for the award and continue to consider the bids. We will announce the new operator in due course.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-07-11T15:40:07.6Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533433/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533433/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533433/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-07-06","East Anglia Railway Line: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the Answer of 7 March 2016 to Question 29384, for what reasons the announcement of the award of the next East Anglia rail franchise has been delayed; and when he plans to make that announcement.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","42115"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533434","Wales Office","false","2016-07-11","<p>We are introducing the Universal Service Obligation, guaranteeing internet connectivity to half a million rural properties throughout the UK that fall outside existing plans. We have also secured deals with the Mobile Network Operators to deliver mobile coverage to 90% of the UK’s landmass and to 95% of premises in Wales.</p><p>Recognising the importance of transport costs to rural communities, we have frozen fuel duty for six successive years, the longest freeze for 40 years.</p><p> </p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2016-07-11T11:58:37.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533434/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533434/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-07-06","Rural Areas: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what steps the Government is taking to improve the (a) electronic and (b) physical connectivity of rural villages in Wales.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","42060"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533435","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-07-11","<p>The figures represent the annual expenditure on Work Choice provision from 2010-11 to 2015-16 and estimated spend from 2016/17 to the end of the programme, based on the existing contracts.</p><p> </p><p>It should be noted that with effect from 2015/16, Work Choice provision also includes costs for the Remploy contract. It is not possible to provide information for the amount spent on supporting disabled people through the work programme as this cannot be separately identified.</p><p> </p><p>2010-11 £32m</p><p>2011-12 £79m</p><p>2012-13 £83m</p><p>2013-14 £86m</p><p>2014-15 £88m</p><p>2015-16 £124m</p><p> </p><p>Total to 2015/16: £492m.</p><p> </p><p>The total over the life of the Work Choice programme is currently estimated to be £645m.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-07-11T14:26:38.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533435/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533435/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-07-06","Employment Schemes: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much his Department spent on supporting disabled people through (a) the work programme and (b) work choice in (i) each year since 2010 and (ii) total since the introduction of those schemes; and what the total cost of support over the lifetime of the two programmes is estimated to be.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","42016"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533436","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-07-12","<p>The in-work progression Randomised Control Trial is currently being expanded following a successful proof of concept stage. It is too early to provide any assessment of its impact.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-07-12T15:41:58.883Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533436/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533436/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-07-06","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of in-work conditionality under universal credit on the number of people offered (a) full-time and (b) part-time employment.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","42028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533437","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-07-11","<p>The data for Employment and Support Allowance (ESA) and Personal Independence Payment (PIP) Mandatory Reconsiderations which have resulted in a decision being changed can be found at:</p><p>Employment and Support Allowance</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/530530/esa-wca-mr-summary-june-2016-tables-version2.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/530530/esa-wca-mr-summary-june-2016-tables-version2.ods</a></p><p>Personal Independence Payment</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/528662/pip-registrations-and-clearances-apr-2016.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/528662/pip-registrations-and-clearances-apr-2016.xls</a></p><p>The breakdown of data you have requested for Birkenhead can only be provided at a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-07-11T16:42:12.313Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533437/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533437/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-07-06","Social Security Benefits: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 30 June 2016 to Question 41331, how many decisions taken on claims for (a) employment and support allowance and (b) personal independence payment have been taken to mandatory reconsideration in (i) Birkenhead and (ii) the UK in each of the past five years; and how many of those mandatory reconsiderations have been successful.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","42057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533438","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-07-13","<p>Motability is an independent charitable organisation, wholly responsible for the Motability Scheme. More detailed information about the operation of the Scheme can be requested from the Director of Motability, Motability, Warwick House, Roydon Road, Harlow, Essex, CM19 5PX.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not provide any funding to Motability so the Scheme does not come at a direct cost to the taxpayer.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-07-13T12:29:24.19Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533438/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533438/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-07-06","Motability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the value for money provided by Motability to (a) disabled people and (b) the public purse.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","42110"
